22/01/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- Police on Monday (January 21st) arrested two colleagues and one officer from the civil emergency Kosovo Protection Corps for a bomb attack on a coffee shop in downtown Pristina last September.
The blast, one of the most powerful in years, killed two people, injured 11 and caused serious damage.
Police said more arrests would follow, but would not discuss a motive.
(AP - 21/01/08)
